<subSubSection id="208D2DD7FF8DFFDC3DE2FE65FC037313" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="68287E5CFF8DFFDC3DE2FE65FC037313" blockId="15.[151,1437,366,825]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<materialsCitation id="D8FF7401FF8DFFDC3DE2FE65FF5C72F7" collectionCode="NHMUK" collectorName="Edward Damel" country="Australia" determinerName="D. J. Brothers" latitude="-27.25" location="Moreton Bay" longLatPrecision="1237" longitude="153.25" municipality="Brisbane" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-male="1" stateProvince="Queensland" typeStatus="lectotype">
This taxon was described from more than one male specimen collected at “Moreton Bay” (collector/s unspecified) and in 
<collectionCode id="0E86E699FF8DFFDC3C01FE09FE2B71F3" box="[292,398,475,501]" collectionName="NHMUK" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">NHMUK</collectionCode>
(p. i). There are two male specimens so identified in that collection; they have appropriate and identical collecting data (accession 58–124: 
<collectingCountry id="10803ECCFF8DFFDC3F94FE2DFCBE721F" box="[689,795,511,537]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Australia</collectingCountry>
, Moreton Bay; coll. 
<collectorName id="C5621B8AFF8DFFDC3EDBFE2DFB0C721F" box="[1022,1193,511,537]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Edward Damel</collectorName>
; bought of S.Stevens) and agree with the description. These are evidently syntypes and I hereby designate one the 
<typeStatus id="B72CC0FEFF8DFFDC398CFDF1FAB6723B" box="[1193,1299,547,573]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">lectotype</typeStatus>
. It bears the following labels: “Lecto- / type” [circular, violet margin, typeset]; “Type” [circular, red margin, typeset]; “58 / 124 [handwritten] // More / ton B” [circular blue label, handwritten, almost indecipherable]; “ 
<taxonomicName id="AF9705DFFF8DFFDC3985FDB9FB507283" authorityName="Albertisi Andre" authorityYear="1896" box="[1184,1269,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mutilla</taxonomicName>
/ aeruginosa / (Type) Sm[ith].” [Smith’s handwriting]; “B.M.TYPE / HYM. [typeset] / 15-631 [handwritten, blue ink]; “= ignita / Smith” [handwritten]; “ 
<typeStatus id="B72CC0FEFF8DFFDC3C96FD61FDF372CB" box="[435,598,691,717]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="AF9705DFFF8DFFDC3F4AFD61FCE172CB" box="[623,836,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeruginosa">Mutilla aeruginosa</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount id="7E91B5D5FF8DFFDC3E68FD61FCC772CB" box="[845,866,691,717]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
/ 
<bibRefCitation id="0C0603ADFF8DFFDC3E59FD61FC5A72CB" author="Smith, F." box="[892,1023,691,717]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref138738" refString="Smith, F. (1879) Descriptions of New Species of Hymenoptera in the Collection of the British Museum. British Museum, London, xxii + 240 pp. [13 December 1879]" type="book" year="1879">Smith 1879</bibRefCitation>
/ det. 
<determinerName id="9DF49298FF8DFFDC3967FD61FB7572CB" box="[1090,1232,691,717]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D.J.Brothers</determinerName>
1981” [my hand- writing].
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation id="D8FF7401FF8DFFDC3DDAFD05FC077313" collectionCode="NHMUK" collectorName="Edward Damel" country="Australia" determinerName="D. J. Brothers" latitude="-27.25" location="Moreton Bay" longLatPrecision="1237" longitude="153.25" municipality="Brisbane" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-male="1" stateProvince="Queensland" typeStatus="paralectotype">
The other specimen has been labelled as a paralectotype. The type locality (
<location id="6D482887FF8DFFDC3968FD05FB4072F7" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:E03ECF4AFF8DFFDC3DB2FEBCFE19733F:6D482887FF8DFFDC3968FD05FB4072F7" box="[1101,1253,727,753]" country="Australia" latitude="-27.25" longLatPrecision="1237" longitude="153.25" municipality="Brisbane" name="Moreton Bay" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" stateProvince="Queensland">Moreton Bay</location>
) is the region of 
<collectingMunicipality id="884CE426FF8DFFDC3DB2FD29FF587313" box="[151,253,763,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brisbane</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AA53B0BEFF8DFFDC3C2CFD29FE357313" box="[265,400,763,789]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Queensland</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="10803ECCFF8DFFDC3CBFFD29FDA47313" box="[410,513,763,789]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Australia</collectingCountry>
(approximately 
<geoCoordinate id="0DA3189BFF8DFFDC3F9FFD28FCBF7313" box="[698,794,762,789]" degrees="27" direction="south" minutes="15" orientation="latitude" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" precision="925" value="-27.25">27°15' S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="0DA3189BFF8DFFDC3E02FD28FC3F7313" box="[807,922,762,789]" degrees="153" direction="east" minutes="15" orientation="longitude" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" precision="925" value="153.25">153°15' E</geoCoordinate>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="208D2DD7FF8DFFDC3E88FD29FE19733F" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="68287E5CFF8DFFDC3E88FD29FE19733F" blockId="15.[151,1437,366,825]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This species is currently placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AF9705DFFF8DFFDC3DB2FCCDFE1C733F" authority="Brothers, 2018" authorityName="Brothers" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,441,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Aglaotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5AE3A24EFF8DFFDC3DB2FCCDFEA2733F" box="[151,263,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Aglaotilla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0C0603ADFF8DFFDC3C2BFCCDFE1C733F" author="Brothers, D. J." box="[270,441,799,825]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="357 - 368" refId="ref133920" refString="Brothers, D. J. (2018) Aglaotilla, a new genus of Australian Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) with metallic coloration. Zootaxa, 4415 (2), 357 - 368. [30 April 2018] https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4415.2.6" type="journal article" year="2018">Brothers, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
